tmax Manual
***********

tmax is an extensible terminal-based text editor written in TypeScript,
running on the Bun runtime.  It follows the Emacs architecture: a
TypeScript core handles terminal I/O, file system operations, and buffer
management, while a built-in Lisp dialect called T-Lisp handles all
editor functionality--commands, modes, key bindings, and extensibility.

