2 Installation
**************

2.1 Prerequisites
=================

tmax requires the Bun (https://bun.sh/) JavaScript/TypeScript runtime.
Bun provides fast startup times and native TypeScript support without a
compilation step.

   Install Bun by following the instructions at <https://bun.sh/>.  On
macOS and Linux, the quickest method is:

     curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash

2.2 Building from Source
========================

Clone the repository and install dependencies:

     # Clone the repository
     git clone https://github.com/mekkamagnus/tmax.git
     cd tmax

     # Install dependencies
     bun install

     # Make the launcher executable
     chmod +x bin/tmax bin/tmaxclient

2.3 Adding to Your PATH
=======================

Add the ‘bin/’ directory to your shell's ‘PATH’ so you can run ‘tmax’
from anywhere:

     echo 'export PATH="$PATH:/path/to/tmax/bin"' >> ~/.bashrc
     source ~/.bashrc

   Replace ‘/path/to/tmax’ with the actual path to your clone.

2.4 Verifying the Installation
==============================

Confirm that tmax is working:

     # Check if tmax is on your PATH
     which tmax

     # Ping a running daemon (or just start the editor)
     tmax --help

     # Run the test suite
     bun test

2.5 Development Scripts
=======================

The following ‘bun’ scripts are available in the project:

‘bun run start’
     Run the editor directly (no daemon).  Accepts a filename argument.
‘bun run dev’
     Run the editor in development mode with auto-reload on file
     changes.
‘bun run repl’
     Start the T-Lisp REPL for interactive experimentation.
‘bun run daemon’
     Start the daemon only (no TUI frame).
‘bun run tui’
     Start the TUI client directly.
‘bun test’
     Run the full test suite.
‘bun run test:ui’
     Run UI tests using the tmux test harness.


